Nueva Andalucía
description: Known as the “Golf Valley,” Nueva Andalucía is Marbella’s most in-demand residential area, combining modern villas, golf-front properties, and vibrant lifestyle. Minutes from Puerto Banús, it’s ideal for investors, expats, and families alike.

name: Los Naranjos
description: Los Naranjos is a prestigious residential enclave nestled in the heart of Marbella’s Golf Valley, just minutes from Puerto Banús. Known for its tranquil ambiance, lush greenery, and proximity to top-tier golf courses like Los Naranjos Golf Club, it blends exclusivity with convenience. The area offers elegant villas, gated communities, international schools, and upscale amenities—ideal for families, holidaymakers, or investors seeking high rental demand and lifestyle appeal.

name: Nueva Alcántara
description: Nueva Alcántara is one of the most desirable residential areas in San Pedro de Alcántara, Marbella. Located just steps from the beach and a short stroll from the vibrant town center, it offers the perfect balance of coastal tranquility and urban convenience. The neighborhood features wide tree-lined avenues, luxury developments, 24-hour security, and proximity to top-tier amenities — including international schools, sports clubs, restaurants, and beach clubs. Ideal for families and year-round living, Nueva Alcántara stands out for its quality of life and long-term investment potential.

description: La Alquería is a rising luxury residential area in Benahavís, just 10 minutes from Puerto Banús. name: Huerta del Prado-La Montua
description:
La Montua is a small, established residential enclave in Marbella (Málaga, Spain), perched just north of the city centre above the Huerta del Prado district.

Its gently sloping streets are lined with mature pine and palm trees, providing both privacy and lush greenery. From here, residents enjoy sweeping panoramic views of the Mediterranean coastline, the Sierra Blanca range and La Concha peak. Despite its peaceful, suburban feel, La Montua lies within easy reach of Marbella’s Old Town, beaches, marina, schools and shops, making it a prized balance of tranquility and convenience

name: La Mairena
description: La Mairena is an upmarket residential enclave perched on the hillside above Elviria in the municipality of Ojén, Málaga. Nestled at approximately 430 m above sea level within the foothills of the Sierra de las Nieves, it benefits from a unique microclimate—cooler summers and mild winters—surrounded by mature pine and cork oak forest. The area offers residents panoramic sea and mountain views, extensive walking and mountain-bike trails, and direct access to the Santa María Golf Club.

name: Bel-Air
description: Bel-Air is a prestigious gated enclave on the western edge of Estepona, set amid mature pine and cork-oak woodlands and offering luxury villas with panoramic sea and golf-course views—all within minutes of the beach, Santa María Golf Club and the town centre, and just a 15-minute drive to Marbella and 10 minutes to Puerto Banús.
